name: Carina Silfverduk
bio:
Carina Silfverduk is the Practice Lead for Agility and a lean six sigma black belt at CAS, a division of the American Chemical Society. She works for Technology Continual Improvement driving positive change throughout the organization.
 
 Carina is first and foremost a lifelong learner; she's an avid reader and who likes working with, learning from and helping others. She is aggressively curious and loves collaborating towards meaningful shared goals.
 
 Agile and Lean since 2003 first as an XP developer then a scrum master/dev and finally as a coach, Carina co-leads the Women in Agile Columbus Chapter.
